<span id="xviii.ii-p7"></span> The Hagarenes or Hagarites were the
posterity of Abraham by Keturah, (who is supposed to have been Hagar,)
whom he married after Sarah’s death. They dwelt on the east of Gilead,
in the vicinity of the Euphrates. In the days of Saul war was made upon
them by the Reubenites, who, after having nearly destroyed them and
expelled them from their country, dwelt in their tents, (<span
id="xviii.ii-p7.1"></span>[1Ch
5:10](../../../bib/kjv/ch1005.htm#010)<span id="xviii.ii-p7.1"></span>..md)
